name: $template_counter fail when > 750
definition:
checks for PRODUCTS:
  - $template_counter: # Template check
      parameters:
        table: PRODUCTS
      fail: when > 750

      template:
        name: template_counter
        description: Counts the amount of rows in a table
        author: Tim Poot
        metric: counter
        query: |-
          SELECT COUNT(*) AS counter FROM ${table}

name: (full_name, email) pairs must be unique

name: (name, category) pairs must be unique
definition:
checks for products:
  - duplicate_count(name, category) = 0:
      name: (name, category) pairs must be unique

  # Note: (product_id, name, category) uniqueness is redundant if product_id is unique,
  # so we drop that triple check.

  # ── (Optional) Domain / Business rules ─────────────────────────

name: ac_max_length
definition:

name: All check statuses are valid
definition:
checks for CHECK_RESULTS:
  - invalid_count(CHECK_STATUS) = 0:
      name: "All check statuses are valid"
      valid values: ['pass', 'fail', 'warn', 'error']
      samples limit: 1000
      attributes:
        dimension: Validity

name: All check types are valid
definition:
checks for CHECK_RESULTS:
  - invalid_count(CHECK_TYPE) = 0:
      name: "All check types are valid"
      valid values: ['row_count', 'missing_count', 'duplicate_count', 'invalid_count',
        'freshness', 'schema']
      samples limit: 1000
      attributes:
        dimension: Validity

  # Freshness and row_count checks omitted to avoid failures on empty table during initial runs

name: status must be one of {paid, pending, failed}
definition:
checks for payments:
  - failed rows:
      name: status must be one of {paid, pending, failed}
      fail condition: status NOT IN ('paid','pending','failed')

  # ── Timestamp logic (paid_ts) ──────────────────────────────────

name: status must not be null
definition:
checks for payments:
  - missing_count(status) = 0:
      name: status must not be null
  # paid_ts can be null when not paid; see conditional checks below

  # ── Accuracy / Ranges / Domains ────────────────────────────────

name: Test_loan_grade_consistency
definition:
checks for CREDIT_DETAILS:
  - failed rows:
      samples limit: 100
      column: LOAN_GRADE
      fail query: "SELECT cd.*\r\nFROM PERSON_DETAILS pd\r\nJOIN CREDIT_DETAILS cd
        ON pd.ID = cd.PERSON_ID\r\nWHERE pd.PERSON_INCOME < 14580 \r\nAND cd.LOAN_GRADE
        IN ('A', 'B')\r\n"
      name: Test_loan_grade_consistency
      identity: c69ed8c8-06b9-41a1-a662-0d9929ef8e29
      fail: when > 0
      attributes:
        dimension: Consistency

name: Test_loan_interest_rate_completeness
definition:
checks for CREDIT_DETAILS:
  - missing_count(LOAN_INT_RATE):
      name: Test_loan_interest_rate_completeness
      identity: 652634cb-07f2-42f7-a1a9-1842a6aa47e5
      fail: when > 0
      attributes:
        dimension: Completeness

name: total_discount <= 5000000
definition:
checks for ORDER_ITEMS:
  - total_discount <= 5000000: # User defined check
      total_discount query: |
        SELECT SUM(TOTAL_PRICE * (DISCOUNT_PERCENT / 100))
        FROM ORDER_ITEMS

name: Valid purchase amount
definition:
checks for PREMIUMS:
  - max(MONTHLY_PREMIUM):
      filter: PRODUCT_ID = 'PROD-310'
      name: Valid purchase amount
      fail: when >= 500

name: Very recent order activity
definition:
checks for ORDERS:
  - freshness(ORDER_DATE) < 7:
      name: "Very recent order activity"
      filter: ORDER_STATUS IN ('pending', 'processing')
      attributes:
        dimension: Timeliness

  # Business logic validation
